        public static boolean epsilonEquals(Tuple2DReadOnly tuple1,
                                    Tuple2DReadOnly tuple2,
                                    double epsilon)
        Tests on a per component basis if the two given tuples are equal to an epsilon.
        Parameters:
        tuple1 - the first tuple. Not modified.
        tuple2 - the second tuple. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance to use when comparing each component.
        Returns:
        true if the two tuples are equal, false otherwise.

      • interpolate

        @Deprecated
public static double interpolate(double a,
                                              double b,
                                              double alpha)
        Deprecated. Use EuclidCoreTools.interpolate(double,double,double) instead
        Performs a linear interpolation from a to b given the percentage alpha.

        result = (1.0 - alpha) * a + alpha * b

        Parameters:
        a - the first value used in the interpolation.
        b - the second value used in the interpolation.
        alpha - the percentage to use for the interpolation. A value of 0 will return a, while a value of 1 will return b.
        Returns:
        the interpolated value.
